      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "How deep is Lewis Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Lewis Smith Lake reaches a maximum depth of 264 feet near the dam, making it the deepest lake in Alabama. The average depth across the lake is considerably shallower, but the deep main channel provides excellent cold-water habitat for striped bass year-round." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "How big is Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Smith Lake covers approximately 21,200 surface acres and has 642 miles of shoreline. It spans three counties — Cullman, Walker, and Winston — and stretches across three main arms fed by the Sipsey Fork of the Black Warrior River." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "How clear is the water at Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Smith Lake is one of the clearest lakes in the southeastern United States. Water visibility frequently exceeds 20 feet under good conditions, fed by cold, clear mountain streams from the Bankhead National Forest. This clarity is the defining characteristic of fishing here — it requires lighter line and more finesse presentations than most Southern reservoirs." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Who owns and operates Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Lewis Smith Lake is owned and operated by Alabama Power Company, which uses it for hydroelectric power generation. Alabama Power controls water levels through the Smith Lake Dam near Jasper, Alabama." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What towns are on Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The primary communities around Smith Lake include Arley (Winston County), Crane Hill (Cullman County), Houston (Cullman County), and Jasper (Walker County) near the dam. The Cullman County side is the most developed with the most marina and dining options." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What fish can you catch at Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Smith Lake is home to spotted bass (the dominant gamefish), landlocked striped bass, black crappie, white crappie, channel catfish, and blue catfish. Spotted bass are what Smith Lake is nationally known for — the clear, cold water creates ideal conditions for them." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is Smith Lake good for bass fishing?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — Smith Lake is one of the premier spotted bass fisheries in the United States. The gin-clear water and deep, structure-rich lake bottom produce quality spotted bass up to 5+ pounds. However, Smith Lake fishes very differently from typical Southern bass lakes — clear water demands finesse tactics, light line, and natural color presentations." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Are there largemouth bass in Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Largemouth bass are present but uncommon at Smith Lake. The cold, clear water doesn't suit them as well as it does spotted bass. Anglers targeting largemouth will have better luck in the shallower, warmer coves in the upper arms of the lake during spring." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the best time of year to fish Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Spring (March through May) is the best all-around season — spotted bass are in prespawn feed, crappie fill the coves, and fish are at their most accessible. Fall (September through November) is the most exciting season, with topwater spotted bass action and spectacular striper blowups as fish chase shad to the surface." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Do I need a fishing license to fish Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. All anglers 16 years of age or older must have a valid Alabama freshwater fishing license. Licenses can be purchased online at outdooralabama.com or at most sporting goods retailers. Always verify current regulations before your trip as rules can change." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can you fish Smith Lake from the bank?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, though bank fishing access is limited compared to boat fishing. Clear Creek Recreation Area (operated by the U.S. Forest Service) provides some public bank access. The dam tailwater area also offers bank fishing opportunities for striped bass, though check regulations before fishing below the dam." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What pound test line should I use at Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "For spotted bass, most experienced Smith Lake anglers use 6 to 8-pound fluorocarbon line. The exceptional water clarity means fish can see heavier line, and fluorocarbon's near-invisibility underwater is a real advantage. For striped bass, heavier braid with a fluorocarbon leader is appropriate." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the best lures for Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "For spotted bass: drop shot rigs, Ned rigs, shaky heads, and small finesse swimbaits in natural colors (green pumpkin, watermelon, smoke). For striped bass: umbrella rigs, large swimbaits, and jigged spoons in deep water. For crappie: small jigs (1/16 to 1/8 oz) and live minnows." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Why does Smith Lake require finesse fishing?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The water clarity at Smith Lake — sometimes exceeding 20 feet of visibility — means fish have a clear view of your presentation. Heavy line, bright unnatural colors, and aggressive power-fishing techniques that work in stained water get ignored or spook fish here. Light fluorocarbon, natural colors, and slower presentations consistently outperform." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What electronics do I need for Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Quality sonar and side-imaging electronics are highly recommended. Smith Lake's complex bottom — rocky bluffs, deep ledges, submerged timber, and channel edges — rewards anglers who can read structure before they start casting. A good mapping chip (Navionics or Garmin) loaded with Smith Lake charts is worth the investment." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is Smith Lake full pool elevation?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Smith Lake's full pool elevation is 510 feet above mean sea level (MSL). Alabama Power targets this level during summer recreational season." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does Smith Lake get drawn down in winter?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Alabama Power typically begins drawing Smith Lake down in fall for flood control and dam maintenance. Winter drawdowns can reach 5 to 8 feet below full pool. Despite the lower water, winter fishing can be excellent — fish concentrate in predictable areas and striper jigging in the deep main channel is highly productive." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Where can I check current Smith Lake water levels?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "FishSmithLake.com displays live water level data sourced from USGS gauge station 02450250 at our water levels page. You can also check Alabama Power's shoreline tool at apcshorelines.com." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "How do water levels affect fishing at Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "At or near full pool (510 ft), fish are spread across all available structure — coves, points, bluffs, and flats. As the lake drops 1 to 3 feet below pool, fish begin concentrating on creek channel edges and deeper points. A significant drawdown of 5+ feet pushes fish to the main lake channel, which actually concentrates them and can make for excellent fishing if you know where to look." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the best fishing spots on Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The most consistently productive areas include: Brushy Creek arm (north end, excellent for crappie and spotted bass), Clear Creek arm (northwest side, exceptional structure fishing), the Houston area (south arm, classic spotted bass ledge fishing), the Arley area (Winston County, less pressure and good crappie habitat), and rocky bluff walls throughout all three arms of the lake." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Are there public boat launches on Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, there are multiple public boat launches across all three counties. Notable options include Arley Boat Landing (Winston County), Clear Creek Recreation Area (U.S. Forest Service, Cullman County), and several Alabama Power-maintained launch facilities." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Are there marinas on Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, several marinas operate on Smith Lake including Trident Marina (Crane Hill), Duskin Point Marina (Jasper area), and others. Most offer fuel, boat storage, and launch access." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can you swim at Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — Smith Lake's exceptional water clarity makes it a popular swimming destination. Smith Lake Park in Cullman County is a popular public swimming area. Many private dock owners also swim from their properties." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is Smith Lake a good place to buy waterfront property?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Smith Lake is consistently one of Alabama's most desirable lakefront real estate markets. The clear water, depth, recreational opportunities, and relative proximity to Birmingham make it attractive. Waterfront property values have appreciated steadily." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Who is the best real estate agent for Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Justin Dyar at justindyar.com is Smith Lake's most recognized waterfront specialist, known locally as \"Mr. Smith Lake.\" He has been selling lakefront property on Smith Lake since 2006 with over 20 years of experience on the water." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What do I need to know about dock permits on Smith Lake?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Docks on Smith Lake require a permit from Alabama Power, which manages the shoreline. The permitting process involves Alabama Power's Shoreline Management department. Visit apcshorelines.com for official permit information." } }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://www.fishsmithlake.com" },
