    }
  ]
}
</script>

  <div style="max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 1rem;">
    <h1 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); color: #1A2E1A; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Smith Lake Fishing FAQ</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; color: #4a5a4a; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">Everything anglers ask about Lewis Smith Lake — answered. From first-timers wondering where to start to experienced bass fishermen looking for local intel, this is the reference page for Smith Lake fishing questions.</p>

    <!-- About the Lake -->
    <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.6rem); color: #2D6A4F; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem;">About the Lake</h2>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">How deep is Lewis Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Lewis Smith Lake reaches a maximum depth of 264 feet near the dam, making it the deepest lake in Alabama. The average depth across the lake is considerably shallower, but the deep main channel provides excellent cold-water habitat for striped bass year-round.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">How big is Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Smith Lake covers approximately 21,200 surface acres and has 642 miles of shoreline. It spans three counties — Cullman, Walker, and Winston — and stretches across three main arms fed by the Sipsey Fork of the Black Warrior River.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">How clear is the water at Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Smith Lake is one of the clearest lakes in the southeastern United States. Water visibility frequently exceeds 20 feet under good conditions, fed by cold, clear mountain streams from the Bankhead National Forest. This clarity is the defining characteristic of fishing here — it requires lighter line and more finesse presentations than most Southern reservoirs.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Who owns and operates Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Lewis Smith Lake is owned and operated by Alabama Power Company, which uses it for hydroelectric power generation. Alabama Power controls water levels through the Smith Lake Dam near Jasper, Alabama.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">What towns are on Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">The primary communities around Smith Lake include Arley (Winston County), Crane Hill (Cullman County), Houston (Cullman County), and Jasper (Walker County) near the dam. The Cullman County side is the most developed with the most marina and dining options.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Fishing Basics -->
    <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.6rem); color: #2D6A4F; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2.5rem;">Fishing Basics</h2>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">What fish can you catch at Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Smith Lake is home to spotted bass (the dominant gamefish), landlocked striped bass, black crappie, white crappie, channel catfish, and blue catfish. Spotted bass are what Smith Lake is nationally known for — the clear, cold water creates ideal conditions for them.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Is Smith Lake good for bass fishing?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Yes — Smith Lake is one of the premier spotted bass fisheries in the United States. The gin-clear water and deep, structure-rich lake bottom produce quality spotted bass up to 5+ pounds. However, Smith Lake fishes very differently from typical Southern bass lakes — clear water demands finesse tactics, light line, and natural color presentations.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Are there largemouth bass in Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Largemouth bass are present but uncommon at Smith Lake. The cold, clear water doesn't suit them as well as it does spotted bass. Anglers targeting largemouth will have better luck in the shallower, warmer coves in the upper arms of the lake during spring.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">What is the best time of year to fish Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Spring (March through May) is the best all-around season — spotted bass are in prespawn feed, crappie fill the coves, and fish are at their most accessible. Fall (September through November) is the most exciting season, with topwater spotted bass action and spectacular striper blowups as fish chase shad to the surface.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Do I need a fishing license to fish Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Yes. All anglers 16 years of age or older must have a valid Alabama freshwater fishing license. Licenses can be purchased online at <a href="https://www.outdooralabama.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color: #2D6A4F;">outdooralabama.com</a> or at most sporting goods retailers. Always verify current regulations before your trip as rules can change.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Can you fish Smith Lake from the bank?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Yes, though bank fishing access is limited compared to boat fishing. Clear Creek Recreation Area (operated by the U.S. Forest Service) provides some public bank access. The dam tailwater area also offers bank fishing opportunities for striped bass, though check regulations before fishing below the dam.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Gear & Technique -->
    <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.6rem); color: #2D6A4F; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2.5rem;">Gear &amp; Technique</h2>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">What pound test line should I use at Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">For spotted bass, most experienced Smith Lake anglers use 6 to 8-pound fluorocarbon line. The exceptional water clarity means fish can see heavier line, and fluorocarbon's near-invisibility underwater is a real advantage. For striped bass, heavier braid with a fluorocarbon leader is appropriate.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">What are the best lures for Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">For spotted bass: drop shot rigs, Ned rigs, shaky heads, and small finesse swimbaits in natural colors (green pumpkin, watermelon, smoke). For striped bass: umbrella rigs, large swimbaits, and jigged spoons in deep water. For crappie: small jigs (1/16 to 1/8 oz) and live minnows.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Why does Smith Lake require finesse fishing?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">The water clarity at Smith Lake — sometimes exceeding 20 feet of visibility — means fish have a clear view of your presentation. Heavy line, bright unnatural colors, and aggressive power-fishing techniques that work in stained water get ignored or spook fish here. Light fluorocarbon, natural colors, and slower presentations consistently outperform.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">What electronics do I need for Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Quality sonar and side-imaging electronics are highly recommended. Smith Lake's complex bottom — rocky bluffs, deep ledges, submerged timber, and channel edges — rewards anglers who can read structure before they start casting. A good mapping chip (Navionics or Garmin) loaded with Smith Lake charts is worth the investment.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Water Levels -->
    <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.6rem); color: #2D6A4F; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2.5rem;">Water Levels</h2>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">What is Smith Lake full pool elevation?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Smith Lake's full pool elevation is 510 feet above mean sea level (MSL). Alabama Power targets this level during summer recreational season.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Does Smith Lake get drawn down in winter?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Yes. Alabama Power typically begins drawing Smith Lake down in fall for flood control and dam maintenance. Winter drawdowns can reach 5 to 8 feet below full pool. Despite the lower water, winter fishing can be excellent — fish concentrate in predictable areas and striper jigging in the deep main channel is highly productive.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Where can I check current Smith Lake water levels?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">FishSmithLake.com displays live water level data sourced from USGS gauge station 02450250 at our <a href="/water-levels" style="color: #2D6A4F;">water levels page</a>. You can also check Alabama Power's shoreline tool at <a href="https://apcshorelines.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color: #2D6A4F;">apcshorelines.com</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">How do water levels affect fishing at Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">At or near full pool (510 ft), fish are spread across all available structure — coves, points, bluffs, and flats. As the lake drops 1 to 3 feet below pool, fish begin concentrating on creek channel edges and deeper points. A significant drawdown of 5+ feet pushes fish to the main lake channel, which actually concentrates them and can make for excellent fishing if you know where to look.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Spots & Access -->
    <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.6rem); color: #2D6A4F; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2.5rem;">Spots &amp; Access</h2>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">What are the best fishing spots on Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">The most consistently productive areas include: Brushy Creek arm (north end, excellent for crappie and spotted bass), Clear Creek arm (northwest side, exceptional structure fishing), the Houston area (south arm, classic spotted bass ledge fishing), the Arley area (Winston County, less pressure and good crappie habitat), and rocky bluff walls throughout all three arms of the lake.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Are there public boat launches on Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Yes, there are multiple public boat launches across all three counties. Notable options include Arley Boat Landing (Winston County), Clear Creek Recreation Area (U.S. Forest Service, Cullman County), and several Alabama Power-maintained launch facilities. See our <a href="/boat-launches" style="color: #2D6A4F;">boat launches page</a> for a full list with locations.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Are there marinas on Smith Lake?</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #334155; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">Yes, several marinas operate on Smith Lake including Trident Marina (Crane Hill), Duskin Point Marina (Jasper area), and others. Most offer fuel, boat storage, and launch access.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="border-left: 3px solid #52B788; padding: 1rem; background: #F7FFF7; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1A2E1A; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Can you swim at Smith Lake?</h3>
